This reinforces the proposal released in October, which specifically targeted increased support for low-cost, lightweight materials for vehicle frames, batteries, inexpensive fuel cells (including new technology for using gasoline to power fuel cells), and advanced internal combustion engines for use in hybrid vehicles.
