In the future, the President's proposal for domestic greenhouse gas emissions trading (modeled after the Clean Air Act's highly successful utility acid rain trading program) could bring new investments in advanced transportation technologies.
Trading rewards U.S. companies that produce cleaner technologies through the sale of emissions reduction "credits" to those who need them to comply with regulatory requirements.
While policies unfold, the scientific need to reduce greenhouse gas emissions will remain, as will the challenges and opportunities this issue presents for clean energy and transportation technologies.
