Clean Cities Program Hits the Airwaves Channel surfers in a few select cities may catch a glimpse of the latest and greatest PBS series on alternative fuels entitled, On the Road to Clean Cities for the 21st Century.
The series, a joint effort of the Clean Cities Program, New Vision Communications, and The Jefferson Energy Foundation, features video segments and panel discussions on current issues in the AFV industry.
Each broadcast is taped in front of a live studio audience and will be packaged as one segment in a series of town hall meetings throughout the country.
The series debuted on December 2 at the University of California Riverside's Studio Theater.
This premiere show was broadcast live to PBS channel KVCR in San Bernardino and Orange Riverside Town Hall Panelists Counties.
